Comment: I was so sad to see how they ruined the best thing sport has to offer. It is very close to my heart since I was a child, something sacred even and I would die to be a part of Olympics in some shape or form, but this was disgusting. Beating into one's head political agendas on the most important sporting event sickens me to my deepest core. All previous opening ceremonies were about culture, pride of nation's history and most of all SPORT. Here it seemed more like some sort of political gathering, rather than olympics. There was NOTHING that could resemble sporting event. And what about those participating? How must they feel? Someone might disagree with those political views beat upon all of us but somehow they have to participate, because how can you not if you spent your whole life pursuing a goal of performing at Olympic Games. I feel sick when I look at it and once again it disgusts me deeply.

Comment: ''Olympics'' is a torch carried through hundreds of years. It is humanity at its best ! Uniting the World with sports games & competitions representing a healthy way of life in the most positive light. It was extremely disappointing to watch the opening ceremony with a direction so far away from artistic, intelligent & elegant style. At the very beginning when the torch was on train carried by a man we are suddenly diverted to a very different story, which became highly political & provocative. Children meeting a ghost on a boat taken to underground skulls to face death,.....rest I don't want to mention but just say etc....Olympics is not & never should be used as a platform for expressing any kind of personal choice. It is a platform of international sports competition. Opening ceremony in my opinion did not look professional ,it looked like a very low budget show that is rushed in a very short time with no effort.I don't think ''Thomas Jolly'' really does understand the context of ''Olympics'' ... I want to watch ''Olympics Opening'' not ''Thomas Jolly'' attitude & personal approach to life. It was a very low taste amateur performance at many levels. No style, no grace which must be ''Olympics'' motto at highest level.Sad!!!
